  ("FA55F5BD-162A-4E68-9D8B-F2A074CB487B","https://www.nps.gov/articles/public-health-officials-ina-hysi.htm","Injury Prevention Specialist: Ina Hysi","Ina Hysi is an Injury Prevention Specialist in the NPS Public Risk Management Program working with parks, regions, and national leadership to reduce injuries in parks through outreach, education, and policy. Learn more about her job and how she became involved with public health in the NPS."),
  ("37667CDA-55D5-4277-9BA3-10B46BFB9E75","https://www.nps.gov/articles/rochelle-williams-assistant-to-the-deputy-director-region-1.htm","Rochelle Williams, Assistant to the Deputy Regional Director, Region 1","Rochelle Williams is the assistant to the Deputy Regional Director of Region 1. She notes how the work of suffragists, both well known and some that should be better known, helped create more opportunities for women like her."),
  ("3FC7BA33-1BEA-48C9-BED9-E363D25FB47E","https://www.nps.gov/articles/tina-short.htm","Tina Short: Listening to the Community","Tina Short was one of the first African American women to serve as a Park Ranger in the National Capital Region. A native of Washington, D.C., Ms. Short spent her career at Fort Dupont Park, the very place she had attended as a day camper and became a Junior Ranger. Short became a well-known figure in the neighborhood, building programs that are still popular to this day."),
  ("974010B8-361C-4BBD-8FE4-43AF74EC341C","https://www.nps.gov/articles/veteran-story-erin-rust.htm","Veteran Story: Erin Rust","'This place is indescribable. There is an immense contrast between the incredibly delicate coral ecosystem and the monumental Fort Jefferson.' A park ranger describes her transition from active duty military to veteran national park ranger."),
  ("31233700-7928-43E8-8C24-15F4CA17071C","https://www.nps.gov/articles/veteran-story-margaret-hollandsworth.htm","Veteran Story: Margaret Hollandsworth","Veterans serve many roles in many places. Meet Margarate A. Hollandsworth and read her story of courage, service, and excellence that she brings to the Natiional Park Service."),
  ("36CD1B1C-FC88-4854-9C55-D2D68ED2F617","https://www.nps.gov/articles/vet-story-d-sumner.htm","Veteran Story: Dael Sumner","Dael Sumner was a U.S. Marine. Currently, she works as a seasonal Park Ranger at Fort Stanwix National Monument in Rome, NY. This is her story."),
  ("9D931DD3-16DF-409E-9AEC-35F194991B95","https://www.nps.gov/articles/000/civil-works-administration.htm","Civil Works Administration","Unveiled on November 8, 1933 as part of the Federal Emergency Relief Administration, the intent of the Civil Works Administration was to provide temporary winter construction work. In 1934, construction of the boundary wall was begun by local men hired under the CWA, causing visitors to enter the park through the visitor center."),
