  ("FA9899D8-BAC3-4725-A6B0-817BEBC5A960","https://www.nps.gov/articles/deskdigs_caffrey.htm","#Sciencedeskdigs: Dissecting Scope","Maria Caffrey, a climatologist who studies ancient microfossils like pollen, diatoms, and charcoal, tells us what we can learn from the past. (Adapted from a post from the Instagram series called #sciencedeskdigs that highlights the stories and work of NRSS scientists)."),
  ("D292E8CC-D1ED-4EEC-9FED-99FF1D78F071","https://www.nps.gov/articles/deskdigs_flanagan.htm","#Sciencedeskdigs: Dragonfly Life Cycle","Ecologist, Colleen Flanagan Pritz explains why dragonflies are important to national parks. (Adapted from a post from the Instagram series called #sciencedeskdigs that highlights the stories and work of NRSS scientists)."),
  ("3D81E526-B940-4A09-8393-7433594007C4","https://www.nps.gov/articles/deskdigs_loar.htm","#Sciencedeskdigs: Species Reference Manual","Alison Loar a Biologist with the Inventory and Monitoring Division explains why she hangs onto a species reference manual from '94. (Adapted from a post from the Instagram series called #sciencedeskdigs that highlights the stories and work of NRSS scientists)."),
  ("8F78C35D-007F-43D9-B337-4CED2D7534C6","https://www.nps.gov/articles/deskdigs_mccracken.htm","#Sciencedeskdigs: Geologic Cross Section","Learn the story of how a request for an old map lead GIP guest scientist, Reba McCracken, to a trove of detailed field notes, maps, and cross sections of geologic features in national parks from the 30s and 40s. (Adapted from a post from the Instagram series called #sciencedeskdigs that highlights the stories and work of NRSS scientists)."),
  ("D506763D-2A0E-45DA-86C3-1FD4C289F29B","https://www.nps.gov/articles/deskdigs_nuessly.htm","#Sciencedeskdigs: Field Boots","These boots are made for wading and that is exactly what Ecologist, Katie Nuessly does! Hear more about how we study invertebrates, like sea stars, in national parks. (Adapted from a post from the Instagram series called #sciencedeskdigs that highlights the stories and work of NRSS scientists)."),
  ("5E7FEF86-E8C5-42B8-906A-B347A8E7238D","https://www.nps.gov/articles/deskdigs_ziegler.htm","#Sciencedeskdigs: Crab Larvae","Tracy Ziegler, a Marine Ecologist, tells us what’s up with the tiny vials on her desk. (Adapted from a post from the Instagram series called #sciencedeskdigs that highlights the stories and work of NRSS scientists)."),
  ("7AC8BA9A-5461-4409-BDF9-8B52D87AC8E0","https://www.nps.gov/articles/donna_johnson.htm","Donna R. Johnson, Professional Engineer; Project Manager for Denver Service Center Design & Construction","I like to think 'imagine if there was no National Park Service,' and what the United States would look like. From that, I like to think I am working at keeping the National Park Service mission strong and making contributions to a much better America, than if we had no Parks."),
  ("23F85E78-95E3-43FE-8084-467A520F02DF","https://www.nps.gov/articles/donna-difolco.htm","Donna DiFolco - Biological Technician","Donna DiFolco is a biological technician for Gates of the Arctic National Park and Preserve and Yukon-Charley Rivers National Preserve, Alaska."),
