  ("566B445E-9A05-4BFB-8EF5-6EF460F1E6E8","https://www.nps.gov/articles/fires-yell.htm","Forest Fires in Yellowstone: the Science of Burning and Regrowth","It was the fall of 1988. Dr. Monica Turner, a 29-year-old staff scientist at Oak Ridge National Laboratory, flew out to Yellowstone National Park to start an experiment in forest ecology. She got her first glimpse of the Park since it had been ravaged by huge fires, the likes of which no one had ever seen."),
