  ("E9F46FEB-66F6-42EA-ACA8-0B624912E882","https://www.nps.gov/articles/re-interpretingdiscoverysite.htm","Re-interpreting the Discovery Site","What is the legacy of colonization? Over the centuries, the lens of history has sharpened. The notion that America was vast and empty, waiting to be discovered and settled by Europeans was based on the pretense that no one of significance was here before. The truth is that indigenous people with thriving and highly developed cultures lived across the continent for thousands of years before colonization started..."),
