  ("A45A5495-D915-4B3C-9EC9-4B40DC6E70C8","https://www.nps.gov/articles/five-years-after-blob-another-marine-heatwave.htm","Five Years After “the Blob,” Scientists Monitor Emergence of Another Marine Heatwave","In 2014-2015, the marine heatwave nicknamed “the Blob” was in full force. Ocean surface temperatures rose almost seven degrees Fahrenheit above average, leading to all kinds of impacts along the West Coast. Now, only five years later, NOAA scientists are tracking another significant marine heatwave that looks similar to the early stages of the Blob."),
